<h2>The <code>&lt;component&gt;</code> Element</h2>
<p>
    <strong>Component</strong> defines a brand-new custom element <em>entirely from HTML</em> — its
    tag name and shadow options live in markup, its <strong>own children are the template</strong>
    (no nested <code>&lt;template&gt;</code> wrapper required), and there is no authored
    <code>class extends HTMLElement</code>. It is the fourth gap Web Components fills, alongside
    <a href="/projects/webcomponents/#scoped-registries">scoped registries</a>,
    <a href="/projects/webcomponents/#injector-integration">injector integration</a>, and
    <a href="/blocks/transient-component/">transient components</a>.
</p>
<p>
    The intended implementation is <strong>not</strong> a browser-side interpreter but a
    deterministic, build-time, AST-based transform — the
    <a href="/adapters/declarative-component/">Declarative Component adapter</a> — that lowers each
    definition to the equivalent class element. Toggle any example below between the declarative
    source you write and the class the adapter emits:
</p>

{{ sourceToggle("user-card") }}
{% highlight "html" %}
<component name="user-card" shadow="open">
  <style>:host { display: block } h3 { margin: 0 }</style>
  <h3><slot name="title">Untitled</slot></h3>
  <slot></slot>
</component>

<!-- used anywhere after the definition -->
<user-card><span slot="title">Ada Lovelace</span><p>First programmer.</p></user-card>
{% endhighlight %}
{{ classSource("user-card") }}
{% highlight "typescript" %}
const TEMPLATE = document.createElement('template');
TEMPLATE.innerHTML =
  `<style>:host { display: block } h3 { margin: 0 }</style>` +
  `<h3><slot name="title">Untitled</slot></h3><slot></slot>`;

class UserCard extends HTMLElement {
  #root = this.shadowRoot;
  connectedCallback() {
    this.#root ??= this.attachShadow({ mode: 'open' });
    if (!this.#root.childNodes.length) this.#root.append(TEMPLATE.content.cloneNode(true));
  }
}
customElements.define('user-card', UserCard);
{% endhighlight %}
{{ endSource() }}

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="status">Status</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        <strong>Concept.</strong> The standard ships with its design forks held
        <strong>open for progressive resolution</strong> — see
        <a href="/backlog/">Open Points (DC-1…DC-10)</a> and the grounding report
        <code>reports/2026-06-03-declarative-component-element.md</code>.
        This page documents <em>contracts</em>; the concrete transform/runtime is the
        reference implementation's job (Frontier UI).
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        <strong>Try it:</strong> the <a href="/demos/component-adapter-demo/">Component Adapter Playground</a>
        runs the transform live — author a definition, see the generated class, and render the element.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="authoring">Authoring contract</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><code>name</code> — <strong>required</strong>. The custom element tag to register (must contain a hyphen).</li>
        <li><code>shadow="open|closed|none"</code> — shadow mode; <code>none</code> renders into light DOM. Maps onto <a href="#standards">Declarative Shadow DOM</a> / <code>attachShadow</code>. Defaults to <code>open</code>. <em>(DC-2)</em></li>
        <li><code>delegates-focus</code> — boolean attribute mapping onto <code>attachShadow({ delegatesFocus: true })</code> / DSD <code>shadowrootdelegatesfocus</code>. Focusing the host (or clicking non-focusable shadow content) moves focus to the first focusable element in the shadow tree. Requires a shadow root (<code>shadow</code> ≠ <code>none</code>).</li>
        <li><code>clonable</code> / <code>serializable</code> — boolean attributes mapping onto <code>attachShadow({ clonable: true })</code> / <code>{ serializable: true }</code> (DSD <code>shadowrootclonable</code> / <code>shadowrootserializable</code>). <code>clonable</code> lets <code>cloneNode()</code> copy the shadow tree; <code>serializable</code> lets <code>getHTML({ serializableShadowRoots: true })</code> include it. Both require a shadow root.</li>
        <li><code>form-associated</code> — boolean attribute; emits <code>static formAssociated = true</code> + <code>this.attachInternals()</code> so the element participates in forms (gets <code>:disabled</code> from a fieldset, form-lifecycle callbacks, <code>form</code>/<code>labels</code> access). Value &amp; validation wiring composes with <a href="/projects/webvalidation/">Web Validation</a> later. <em>(DC-12)</em></li>
        <li><code>default-role="…"</code> — sets the element's <strong>default</strong> ARIA semantics via <code>internals.role</code> (e.g. <code>default-role="slider"</code>). An instance <code>role=</code> attribute still overrides it for assistive tech. ARIA role token only. <em>(DC-13)</em></li>
        <li><code>default-aria-*="…"</code> — the rest of the string-valued <code>ElementInternals</code> default-ARIA surface beyond role (e.g. <code>default-aria-label</code>, <code>default-aria-disabled</code>, <code>default-aria-has-popup</code>, <code>default-aria-value-now</code>), mapped through to <code>internals.aria*</code> in the constructor — the same map-through shape as <code>default-role</code>. Kebab → camel (<code>default-aria-has-popup</code> → <code>ariaHasPopup</code>); an instance <code>aria-*=</code>/IDL still overrides (these are <em>defaults</em> in the ARIA cascade). Unknown keys are rejected. <em>(#853)</em></li>
        <li><code>preserve-on-move</code> — boolean attribute; emits an empty <code>connectedMoveCallback()</code>. Defining it makes <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/moveBefore"><code>Element.moveBefore()</code></a> relocate the element <strong>atomically</strong> — focus, media playback, iframes, and shadow state are preserved instead of being torn down and rebuilt. <em>(DC-15)</em></li>
        <li>The component's <strong>own children are the template</strong> — the render source, cloned into the shadow (or light) tree on first connect. May contain <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;slot&gt;</code>. <strong>No nested <code>&lt;template&gt;</code> is required.</strong> A childless <code>&lt;component&gt;</code> registers an element with an empty template. <em>(DC-11, DC-9)</em></li>
        <li>A lone direct-child <code>&lt;template&gt;</code> is supported as the <strong>explicit, inert form</strong> — needed only when content must stay inert before the build transform runs (un-built runtime delivery, or table-fragment markup like <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> the parser would otherwise drop). Both forms lower to byte-identical output. <em>(DC-11)</em></li>
        <li>The <code>&lt;component&gt;</code> element <strong>registers its definition then removes itself</strong> — no wrapper node remains. <em>(DC-3)</em></li>
        <li><code>observe="attr-1 attr-2 …"</code> — declares the attributes the element reflects into its template. Lowers to a static <code>observedAttributes</code> getter plus an <code>attributeChangedCallback</code> that updates each bound text hole. A <code>{% raw %}{{ attr }}{% endraw %}</code> interpolation in the template binds that observed attribute's value to a generated text node — <strong>one-way, attribute → text content only</strong> (no event/output binding, no nested property access at this tier). The expression inside <code>{% raw %}{{ }}{% endraw %}</code> parses with the <a href="/projects/webexpressions/">Web Expressions</a> grammar — the <code>CustomExpressionParser</code> restricted sublanguage — so this build-time path and the runtime <a href="/blocks/interpolation-text-node/">interpolation text node</a> share <strong>one grammar contract</strong>; only <em>when</em> they resolve differs. The compile-time lowering bakes a per-hole updater with no injector chain — the <strong>unplugged twin</strong> of the runtime interpolation path, reusing the grammar, not the runtime registry resolution. <em>(DC-4 B1)</em></li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="standards">Web Standards Alignment</h3>
    <table>
        <tr><th>Standard</th><th>Status</th><th>How We Adopt It</th></tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Components/Using_custom_elements">Custom Elements v1</a></td>
            <td>Baseline</td>
            <td>Definition lowers to an autonomous element + <code>customElements.define()</code>. Autonomous only (Safari refuses customized built-ins).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/template#shadowrootmode">Declarative Shadow DOM</a></td>
            <td>Baseline 2024</td>
            <td><code>shadow="open|closed"</code> maps onto <code>attachShadow</code> / DSD; the <code>&lt;template&gt;</code> becomes shadow content.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/slot">Slots</a></td>
            <td>Baseline</td>
            <td>Content projection is native — use <code>&lt;slot&gt;</code> directly; no custom projection layer.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://github.com/WICG/webcomponents/blob/gh-pages/proposals/Scoped-Custom-Element-Registries.md">Scoped Registries</a></td>
            <td>Stage 2 Proposal</td>
            <td>Tier-2 <code>scope</code> attribute composes with the project's Scoped Registries section; global by default.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_components/Using_custom_elements#responding_to_attribute_changes">Observed attributes</a></td>
            <td>Baseline</td>
            <td><code>observe=</code> lowers to a static <code>observedAttributes</code> + <code>attributeChangedCallback</code>; <code>{% raw %}{{ }}{% endraw %}</code> text holes update one-way from those attributes (DC-4 B1).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><a href="https://github.com/WICG/webcomponents/issues/1009">Declarative Custom Elements</a></td>
            <td>Stalled strawman</td>
            <td>Prior art (<code>&lt;definition&gt;</code>). We choose <code>&lt;component&gt;</code> and ship the static tier now, composing unshipped binding primitives later.</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</section>

