    </table>
</section>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="features">Feature Inventory</h3>
    <table>
        <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Disposition</th><th>Tier</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Register element by <code>name</code> from markup</td><td>built-in</td><td>1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Shadow template (<code>shadow="open|closed"</code>, DSD-aligned)</td><td>built-in</td><td>1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Light-DOM template (<code>shadow="none"</code>)</td><td>built-in</td><td>1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Focus delegation (<code>delegates-focus</code> → <code>attachShadow</code> <code>delegatesFocus</code>)</td><td>built-in (maps native DSD attr)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Clonable / serializable shadow (<code>clonable</code> / <code>serializable</code>)</td><td>built-in (maps native DSD attr)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Form participation (<code>form-associated</code> → <code>attachInternals</code>)</td><td>built-in (DC-12)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Default ARIA semantics (<code>default-role</code> → <code>internals.role</code>)</td><td>built-in (DC-13)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Default ARIA surface beyond role (<code>default-aria-*</code> → <code>internals.aria*</code>)</td><td>built-in (#853)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Custom states (<code>:state()</code> seeding/toggling)</td><td>defer (DC-14)</td><td>3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Form value &amp; validation wiring</td><td>compose (<a href="/projects/webvalidation/">Web Validation</a>)</td><td>3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>State-preserving moves (<code>preserve-on-move</code> → <code>connectedMoveCallback</code>)</td><td>built-in (DC-15)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Slots / content projection</td><td>compose (native <code>&lt;slot&gt;</code>)</td><td>1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Build-time AST transform → class</td><td>adapter</td><td>1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Observed attributes → reflect to template (<code>observe=</code> → <code>observedAttributes</code> + <code>{% raw %}{{ }}{% endraw %}</code> text holes, one-way)</td><td>built-in (DC-4 B1)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Reactive bindings in template (event/output, nested paths, <code>if</code>/<code>each</code>)</td><td>compose (<a href="/blocks/for-each/">for-each</a> / Web Expressions)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Scoped registration (<code>scope</code>)</td><td>compose (Scoped Registries)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Script enhancement hook (<code>behavior</code>/<code>extends</code>)</td><td>design-pending (DC-5 policy ratified; resolution mechanism <a href="/backlog/852-behavior-extends-tier-2-enhancement-hook-on-component-dc-5-r/">#852</a>)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Live in-browser transform in the toggle</td><td>defer</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Inherit / extend another <code>&lt;component&gt;</code></td><td>compose</td><td>3</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        Tier 1 ships the static, DSD-aligned definition. Tiers 2–3 <strong>compose</strong> with
        other Web Everything standards as they mature — they are not reimplemented here.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="light-dom">Light-DOM components (<code>shadow="none"</code>)</h3>
    <p>When a component needs no style encapsulation, skip the shadow root entirely:</p>
    {{ sourceToggle("byline") }}
{% highlight "html" %}
<component name="x-byline" shadow="none">
  <small><slot></slot></small>
</component>
{% endhighlight %}
    {{ classSource("byline") }}
{% highlight "typescript" %}
const TEMPLATE = document.createElement('template');
TEMPLATE.innerHTML = `<small><slot></slot></small>`;

class XByline extends HTMLElement {
  connectedCallback() {
    if (!this.querySelector('small')) this.append(TEMPLATE.content.cloneNode(true));
  }
}
customElements.define('x-byline', XByline);
{% endhighlight %}
    {{ endSource() }}
</section>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="element-internals">Element internals (<code>form-associated</code>, <code>default-role</code>)</h3>
    <p>
        <code>attachInternals()</code> is the platform's imperative-only surface for form participation,
        default ARIA semantics, and custom states — it has no HTML form today. <code>&lt;component&gt;</code>
        adds the two highest-value pieces declaratively: <code>form-associated</code> opts the element into
        forms, and <code>default-role</code> declares its default accessibility role. Custom states
        (<code>:state()</code>) and form value/validation wiring remain tier-2/3 (DC-14, compose with Web
        Validation).
    </p>
    {{ sourceToggle("rating") }}
{% highlight "html" %}
<component name="x-rating" shadow="open" form-associated default-role="slider">
  <span><slot>★</slot></span>
</component>
{% endhighlight %}
    {{ classSource("rating") }}
{% highlight "typescript" %}
const TEMPLATE = document.createElement('template');
TEMPLATE.innerHTML = `<span><slot>★</slot></span>`;

class XRating extends HTMLElement {
  static formAssociated = true;
  #internals = this.attachInternals();
  #root = this.shadowRoot;
  constructor() {
    super();
    this.#internals.role = 'slider';
  }
  connectedCallback() {
    this.#root ??= this.attachShadow({ mode: 'open' });
    if (!this.#root.childNodes.length) this.#root.append(TEMPLATE.content.cloneNode(true));
  }
}
customElements.define('x-rating', XRating);
{% endhighlight %}
    {{ endSource() }}
</section>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="composition">Composition</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="/blocks/transient-component/">Transient Component</a> — <code>&lt;component&gt;</code> reuses the self-removal lifecycle; transient elements <em>resolve</em> to native HTML, this <em>defines</em> a reusable element.</li>
        <li><a href="/blocks/for-each/">For Each</a> &amp; Web Expressions — supply tier-2 reactive bindings and <code>if</code>/<code>each</code> inside the template (DC-4). The one-way <code>observe=</code> / <code>{% raw %}{{ }}{% endraw %}</code> attribute→text path (DC-4 B1) is the <strong>unplugged compile-time twin</strong> of the runtime <a href="/blocks/interpolation-text-node/">interpolation text node</a>: it reuses the Web Expressions grammar contract but bakes a static per-hole updater at build time instead of resolving through the runtime registry.</li>
        <li><a href="/projects/webinjectors/">Web Injectors</a> — a defined element resolves services/contexts from the DOM tree, like any custom element.</li>
        <li><a href="/projects/webcomponents/#ssr-contract">SSR contract</a> — a build emits the element's Declarative Shadow DOM; the definition itself is build-time.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="section-card">
    <h3 id="open-questions">Open questions (progressive resolution)</h3>
    <p>
        None of the design forks are resolved by fiat. Each is tracked as a
        <code>decision</code> thread in the <a href="/backlog/">backlog</a> (DC-1…DC-15) and in the
        grounding report's Open Points Register, carrying a <em>current recommendation</em> only —
        tag name vs Vue ambiguity (DC-1), <code>shadow</code> spelling (DC-2), registration timing
        (DC-3), reactive depth (DC-4), the scripting hook (DC-5), adapter placement (DC-6), toggle
        interactivity (DC-7), Protocol extraction (DC-8), implicit empty template (DC-9), the
        explicit-empty round-trip sub-decision (DC-10), children-as-template default vs the
        inert <code>&lt;template&gt;</code> escape hatch (DC-11), and the ElementInternals surface —
        <code>form-associated</code> (DC-12), <code>default-role</code> spelling (DC-13), and custom
        states (DC-14); and state-preserving moves <code>preserve-on-move</code> (DC-15).
    </p>
</section>
